cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper addresses a core problem in computer vision, specifically the detection and description of 2D feature points for image matching. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new training methodology that uses reinforcement learning principles, which suggests a possible fit with categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper addresses the task of relative pose estimation between a pair of images, which could potentially fit with categories such as cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
